# Cereaper conventions

Cereaper is a native Swift macOS desktop agent. Read `AGENTS.md` for the full spec.

## Architecture boundaries (do not cross casually)
- `LLMModel.swift` ‚Äî provider-neutral message/content-block/tool/timing model.
- `CerebrasClient.swift` ‚Äî Cerebras Chat Completions adapter only. Keep provider oddities here.
- `Agent.swift` ‚Äî the agent loop, step budget, fail-closed termination.
- `Tools.swift` ‚Äî tool protocol + `read`, `bash`, `write`, `edit`, `screenshot`, `image_look`, `computer_use`.
- `ComputerUse.swift` ‚Äî native macOS Accessibility API. AX-grounded, fail-closed.
- `QA.swift` ‚Äî hero build‚Üírun‚Üídrive‚Üíverify‚Üíreport flow.
- `Race.swift` ‚Äî Cerebras-vs-GPU timing harness.
- `App*` files ‚Äî AppKit UI only. No agent logic here.

## Gemma 4 on Cerebras
- Model ID: `gemma-4-31b`. Endpoint: `https://api.cerebras.ai/v1`. Key: `CEREBRAS_API_KEY`.
- Reasoning OFF by default. Set `reasoning_effort` (`low`/`medium`/`high`) only when needed; `none` keeps it off.
- Image input: base64 data URIs via `image_url` blocks. No hosted image URLs.
- Capture `time_info` (TTFT, tokens/sec) on every completion ‚Äî the race harness depends on it.

## Reliability defenses (build in from day one)
- Strict tool-call-only outputs.
- Hard step budget per run.
- `final_answer` tool forces termination.
- Stop sequences to truncate leaked reasoning.

## Safety (non-negotiable)
- Fail closed: if an AX target isn't exposed, stop and report. Never guess coordinates.
- Confirmation gate before any irreversible action (submit/post/send/delete/file).
- Demo with burner accounts. No secrets/notifications on screen.
- AX-friendly apps only: Safari, Notes, Finder, Terminal, the agent's own generated app.
- Always keep a pre-recorded fallback run for the live demo.

## Build
- `swift build` before declaring a change complete. `swift run` to launch. `swift test` for tests.
- `tau-reference/` is inspiration only ‚Äî gitignored, never imported or linked.
